'''Robert Burn''' (b. 1937) is an Australian [[Natural history|naturalist]] and [[Citizen science|citizen scientist]]. He has identified approximately 100 species of [[Nudibranch|nudibranchs]] and has co-authored around 100 papers published in scientific journals spanning sixty years. his first solo publication, ''Nudibranchs and related molluscs'', was published by CSIRO Publishing in February 2016.<ref>{{Cite book|url=http://www.publish.csiro.au/book/7531/|title=Nudibranchs and Related Molluscs|last=Burn|first=Robert|date=2016-02-01}}</ref> The nudibranch genus ''[[Burnaia]]'' is named in his honor.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.queenslandcountrylife.com.au/story/3696876/meet-mr-mollusc/|title=Meet Mr Mollusc|last=Smith|first=Bridie|date=2016-01-31|work=Queensland Country Life|access-date=2017-08-30|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.smh.com.au/technology/sci-tech/meet-mr-mollusc-20160128-gmgly5.html|title=Meet Mr Mollusc|last=Smith|first=Bridie|date=2016-01-31|work=The Sydney Morning Herald|access-date=2017-08-30|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/189971551|title=Nudibranchs and related molluscs|last=Burn|first=Robert|last2=|first2=|date=|publisher=Museum Victoria|year=2015|isbn=9780980381382|location=Melbourne, Victoria, Australia|pages=|language=English}}</ref>

